# Filament admin (src/app/Filament/**)

- Filament is the **preferred** admin implementation surface for new work.
- Use **Filament 5** APIs and patterns in this project.
- Keep resources/pages/widgets consistent with existing structure under `app/Filament/Resources/**`.
- For Filament 5 resources, prefer extracting table definitions to dedicated `Tables/*Table` classes with a `configure(Table $table): Table` method.
- For backed enums implementing `Filament\Support\Contracts\HasLabel`, prefer `->options(SomeEnum::class)` when every case belongs in the select.
- When only a subset of cases should appear, keep the allowed list in domain logic on the enum and build select options from it (e.g. `OrderMethod::shortLinkSelectOptions()`). Use `->disableOptionWhen()` only when most cases stay enabled and a few should be excluded (see `FeedbackType::isDisabled()`).
- When migrating features from legacy admin:
  - Reuse domain logic from `App\` services/models; avoid copying controller-heavy patterns.
  - Keep backward compatibility in data/permissions; ensure navigation and labels match existing admin expectations.
- If you change permissions/roles, check how **Filament Shield** is used (`bezhansalleh/filament-shield`).
